          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <placeName>Easton</placeName>
                                        <date>April 12/47</date>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Mr I. Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Revd Sir. I have been requested by the
                                        officers<lb/> of the <placeName>Easton</placeName>
                                        Congregation to write to you about<lb/> an affair touching
                                        the <persName>Hart family</persName>. They have a<lb/>
                                        burial ground here, which they granted to the<lb/>
                                        congregation to make use of and also to any stranger<lb/>
                                        who should be a jew. The <sic>borrough</sic> not-long
                                        since<lb/> passed a law that the owners of the property
                                        situate<lb/> in the street where <del>the</del> our
                                        synagogue is, have to get<lb/> pavements made. The
                                        calculation is, that a pavement in<lb/> front of the burial
                                        ground would cost about 60 dollars.<lb/> The congregation
                                        would therefore inform the <persName>Hart
                                        family</persName><lb/> of this new regulation and wish to
                                        hear their intentions.<lb/> In want of proper information to
                                        whom to write about<lb/> this you are respectfully desired
                                        to apprize some<lb/> of the members of the family of what is
                                        stated above,<lb/> and please to let us know as soon as
                                        convenient<lb/> the arrangements they intend to make.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I have received your books some time ago, I<lb/>
                                        shall also write to my brother about the subscription<lb/>
                                        of the Occident.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">I have the honor</p>
                              <p rend="indent(4)">to be yours respectfully</p>
                              <p rend="indent(5)">
                                        <persName role="author">A. B. Arnold</persName>
                              </p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Revd Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <placeName>No 118 South 4<hi rend="sup">th</hi>
                                                  Street</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">
                                        <placeName>Philad.</placeName>
                              </p>
